With deep sadness I wanted to share with all of you that @exileintl Peace Lives Rehabilitation Center (which homes and provides therapy for 50+ children orphaned by war / rescued from child soldiering in the DRC) burnt to the ground recently. The damage destroyed the boys dormitory, water tanks, and carpentry building. Part of the girls dorm, children’s home, and office building were damaged. As well as the Ninja Warrior course I was able to partner with them in 2019 to build with the help and donations from all of you! 

🚨the EI team is currently trying to arrange housing for the 50+ children and who live at this center. Given the escalating war in Eastern Congo, we need to rebuild immediately. 

‼️ A generous donor has offered to match up to $100,000! Visit exileinternational.org or text PEACELIVES to 44321 to receive a link to give sent straight to your phone.

Thank you so much for the help if you are able to give 🙏

SHE’S A WHOLE DOCTOR OF PHYSICAL THERAPY!!!

Tawana Jackson DPT 👩🏾‍⚕️🎉🥳🍾

For as long as I have known her, she has been putting everyone she loves ahead of herself, her dreams, and even her own well being sometimes. 

Tee received her Doctorate of Physical Therapy 10 years ago, while simultaneously fighting through an unimaginable loss in her life. Not too many years later, she moved into my parents home with me to care for my own mother through hospice. She has put her dreams aside year after year. Returning to the world of PT to get her license 10 years after graduating was daunting, but watching her go into the office to study with diligence and consistency was incredible to witness for me. I had the privilege of watching her grow in confidence along the way, and the transformation has been stunning. I’ve just learned so much from watching her determination and I know I will carry these lessons with me my entire life, and still continue to be inspired by her. 

I just couldn’t be more proud. 

Did you hear me say SHES A WHOLE LICENSED DOCTOR OF PHYSICAL THERAPY. 

Make sure to send her a message, call her, text her, comment below!!! She deserves all of the celebration! Xoxo 🥳

I take collagen rather than whey protein because collagen benefits your whole body systemically, strengthening and repairing: muscles, bones, ligaments, tendons, hair, and skin... while whey protein is mainly known to support muscle growth. Collagen plays such a crucial role in the health and healing within us - making up 30% of your body’s protein and literally holding our bodies together. As I take Sparkle Wellness collagen, I’m building up and healing so many vital components of my body! Recapping 2023! 

What an unreal year this has been. 

From attempting to break a world record on the @guinnessworldrecords television show in Italy, to competing in the @govgames in Dubai on a team with the most amazing athletes I know, to competing on American Ninja Warrior for my 6th season (I think?🤭) and qualifying for the National finals for my 4th time, to working my dream job in France and Germany, to being on Team USA in international competition… to diligently working towards my climbing and fitness goals at @inspirerockspring and dipping my toes into the parkour world with the help of my friends. 

I just feel so immensely thankful for each and every opportunity and so very proud of what it took for me to get here. 

So much to say about each of these experiences so I might have to follow up with thoughts later on. 

For now, I’m training to make it possible for 2024 to be an even better year 💪 much love to each and every person supporting me on my journey.

I hope you feel P O W E R F U L today. 

In whichever ways you need it most ✨

•I’m feeling powerful in my ability to:
1. Change my habits, my perspective, & my focus.
2. Improve my character, recognizing cognitive dissonance within myself, & seeing ways I’ve allowed my character to falter, so I can build it back up.
3. Forgive those who have wronged me. 
4. Never give up on my health. 
5. Love without holding anything back. 

What ways are you feeling powerful today?
